        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 4:42PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pleasant Grove, or 9 miles south of Senatobia, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasant Grove, Sardis, Batesville, Horatio, McGhee, John W Kyle
State Park, Como, and Ballentine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
